  "prompt": "What do Delhi citizens think of Arvind Kejriwal? Do you think your decision of electing him as CM is a right decision?",
  "response": "Public opinion on Arvind Kejriwal, the Chief Minister of Delhi and leader of the Aam Aadmi Party (AAP), is quite varied among citizens. Many supporters appreciate his focus on education, healthcare, and social welfare programs, highlighting initiatives like free healthcare, improved public education, and reduced electricity tariffs. These policies have garnered a significant following, particularly among lower and middle-class residents.\n\nOn the other hand, some critics point to issues such as governance challenges, ongoing debates about the central government's intervention in Delhi's affairs, and concerns over the efficacy of some of his policies. There are also opinions that express frustration over political confrontations with the central government and the perception that his administration could be more effective if it were less divisive.\n\nAs for whether electing him as CM was the right decision, it depends on individual perspectives regarding his policies, governance style, and the priorities of Delhi citizens. Supporters would argue that he has brought positive changes, while critics might contend that different leadership could yield better results.\n\nUltimately, assessment of his leadership and policies will vary among citizens based on their personal experiences and political beliefs.",
